ultra-sociality as cooperation
Ultra-sociality is the ability of humans to cooperate in large groups of genetically unrelated individuals.

ultra-sociality as cooperation
Ultra-sociality is the ability of humans to cooperate in large groups of genetically unrelated individuals.
Cooperation in small-scale societies relies on face-to-face interactions, so large brains were required to store and process social interactions data.

ultra-sociality as cooperation
Ultra-sociality is the ability of humans to cooperate in large groups of genetically unrelated individuals.
Cooperation in small-scale societies relies on face-to-face interactions, so large brains were required to store and process social interactions data.
However, once a human group attains the size of 100200 individuals, human brain becomes overwhelmed with the complexity of social computation.

ultra-sociality as cooperation
Ultra-sociality is the ability of humans to cooperate in large groups of genetically unrelated individuals.
Cooperation in small-scale societies relies on face-to-face interactions, so large brains were required to store and process social interactions data.
However, once a human group attains the size of 100200 individuals, human brain becomes overwhelmed with the complexity of social computation.
For group size to increase beyond the few hundred individuals, we had to break through the barriers imposed by face-to-face sociality.
